editionStmt.edition: This text is an enriched version of the TCP digital transcription A44860 of text R220141 in the English Short Title Catalog (Wing H3256). Textual changes and metadata enrichments aim at making the text more computationally tractable, easier to read, and suitable for network-based collaborative curation by amateur and professional end users from many walks of life. The text has been tokenized and linguistically annotated with MorphAdorner. The annotation includes standard spellings that support the display of a text in a standardized format that preserves archaic forms ('loveth', 'seekest'). Textual changes aim at restoring the text the author or stationer meant to publish.

notesStmt.note: Verse: MOst Reverend Lords, the Churches Joy and Wonder ...
In this edition, the "M" in "MOst", on the first line of text, is unornamented, and "Finis" is under the second column.
A satire on two Puritan divines ejected under the Act of Uniformity, 1662.
Reproductions of originals in the Harvard University Library and British Library.
